comment: Thanks to JMiracle for sharing... Solid, not spectacular..
Lacks flavor, bitter on the end, pass on this one!
This was a little disappointing.  Not much flavor.
Very smooth. Flavor starts faint and builds.
No real character to it but not overly cheap tasting either.  The bottle is the best thing about this bourbon.  May become a mixer for cocktails.
Light with notes of vanilla. A little bite on the end
Similar to old Forrester, lots of vanilla, some oak, short finish.

[02.08.2017] Tolerable if free. Turned down a lot of go-tos to try this and check off my list in a bar with poor service and loud music - Madison, WI. Smooth and mostly flavorless, this was like taking a good corn whiskey, diluting with city water and putting in a used barrel for a while. Don't bother.
Terrible, something was sour off the front...then the finish was so mild it wasn't worth the time and effort to pallet. Pass on this one for sure.😜
This is the worst bourbon I have ever had. It's off on color taste and aroma. Total crap. It's the first bourbon I can t find anything good about, except the bottle. That's cool.
Gave it to my dad for his bday
Watered down taste , stale .  Agree that only redeeming quality is the bottle—- for those who remember watching Dallas!
Smells like a nice, 4-star hotel room. I know that's weirdly specific. On the tongue, unique, plastic and organ meats. But not in a bad way. Smooth, light. Short finish. 7/12/17
80 proof and a good taster.  Kentucky hug all over first sip, but mellows out in the end.  12/24/18 Christmas Eve from Marcus.

Tried it in the Glencairn glass.
Overpoweringly floral and chemical.
Seriously tasted bad. Like crayons.
Sadly, no negative stars.

Two months later.
Red plastic cup. Vastly improved. Actually drinkable. I don’t know what to say.
No, it’s a two star rating.
Very thin, no burn whatsoever.  Slight vanilla taste.  A bit of tobacco in it as well
Light nose with mellow flavor. A linger but no real front heat
Very light not a lot of burn on it. Very light caramel hints. I like it because it is soft a nice introduction for people new to bourbon.
Grain forward. Fairly harsh but not overly so. Not a sipper, but could make an acceptable cocktail if the recipe doesn’t mind the grain flavors.
It got a 2* because I like the bottle. Drain pour
A little too light for a bourbon. Does have a nice aftertaste. Definitely has a feel of a caramel finish, but sugar free, which isn't a bad thing.

Seems "thin" overall. Tried neat at first. On the nose was a vegetal smell and it had a rye/grain forward taste, with a quick finish. Added a standard ice cube per roughly 2 shots of this liquor and it changed the flavor a bit for the better: light notes of vanilla, cocoa powder, smooth...still a quick finish. This will be a one time buy because there's better out there on the market at this price point.
Solid for the money. Nothing amazing but definitely worth drinking. More than 1 glass. Hahahah
I guess not bad for cooking with.
Cool bottle. Taste is so so.
Standard bourbon. Brown sugar, low proof
